The Vice President called the Presidents of Colombia and Mexico to discuss the President's announcement on U.S. Cuba policy changes. The Vice President discussed the historic changes to U.S. Cuba policy, including re-establishing diplomatic relations, facilitating travel and increasing remittances, increasing U.S. participation in Cuba's telecommunications sector, and easing restrictions on providing U.S. goods and services to Cubans in third countries. The Vice President also mentioned that the United States would pursue discussions with Cuba and Mexico to address the unresolved maritime boundary in the Gulf of Mexico. Additionally, the Vice President conveyed the President's intent to participate in the April 2015 Summit of the Americas in Panama as long as Cuban civil society is allowed to participate and human rights and democracy are part of the agenda. Both President Santos and President Pe√±a Nieto praised the President's courage and committed to supporting the initiative.